==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Quartenylic
<hw>Quar"ten*yl"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Quartene</ets> + <ets>-yl</ets> + <ets>-ic</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or designating, an acid of the
acrylic acid series, metameric with crotonic acid, and obtained as a
colorless liquid; -- so called from having four carbon atoms in the
molecule. Called also <xex>isocrotonic acid</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

